element_texts.text:
1860
Wednesday, August 1  Charles three years old.  Dr. Burbank left us in A.M.  George and I to John Kimbulls V L Mills.
Thursday August 2 Wrote to Isaac, sewed on mother's dress.  Rode to P.G. and called on Mrs. Taylors and Miss Smith and supper at Mrs. Bnylarms [?].  Call at Mr. Burnharns and Mrs Swords.
Friday August 3 Finished Mothers dress in the am.  Nap after dinner.  Peas from Mr. Lewis.  Father and Mother rode to Mr. Fullers and Penbys [?]

Saturday August  4  Augustes come with mail carrier in P. M. Hovel rider Letter from Isaac  George Letter from F.
Sabbath August 5 To meeting all day and to hear Mr. Coburn at five – Subject  Life and Character of Adonirum Judson – George preached "Have Faith in God"  in the AM and Joyfulness Praise God in PM
Monday August 6 Went to Dear Perkins in the AM Mr. Bristin and sister called in the evening.
